#bitcoin has the power to obsolete banks and other middlemen which provide trust in many financial transactions.
because #bitcoin is peer to peer and mathematically secure it is a trust dis-mediator.
this means #bitcoin can be mathematically proven to be secure  which gives it an advantage over the traditional banking system.
#bitcoin is secured by #cryptography  the mathematics of hiding the meanings of messages.
#bitcoin is powered by a technology called the blockchain.
#bitcoin isn't controlled by anyone so it is optimized for the benefit of its users. it is not subject to inflation by central bank decree.
#bitcoin transactions are recorded pseudonymously so that business can be conducted privately  and free of censorship.
#bitcoin is a peer to peer #network meaning that it is agreed upon and sustained by anyone willing to run the open-source #bitcoin software.
what are the advantages of bitcoin over services like online banking or paypal?
bitcoin is digital money that you can store and send online that is not controlled by a central authority like a bank  or nation-state.
